==English==

===Etymology===
From {{etyl|enm}} {{term|spenden|lang=enm}}, from {{etyl|ang}} *{{term||spendan|lang=ang}} (attested in compounds {{term|aspendan|āspendan|to spend|lang=ang}}, {{term|forspendan||to use up, consume|lang=ang}}), from {{etyl|gem-pro|en}} {{recons|spendanan|lang=gem-pro}}, {{recons|spendōnan||to spend|lang=gem-pro}}, borrowed from {{etyl|la}} {{term|expendere|expendere|to weigh out|lang=la}}. Cognate with {{etyl|goh|-}} {{term|spenton|spentōn|to consume, use, spend|lang=goh}} (whence {{etyl|de|-}} {{term|spenden||to donate, provide|lang=de}}), {{etyl|dum|-}} {{term|spenden||to spend, dedicate|lang=nl}}, Old {{etyl|is|-}} {{term|spenna||to spend|lang=is}}.

